# WebSocket endpoint of the GoalFlow cloud agent (the hub).
#
# LEAVE THIS UNSET for the common case. The UI auto-derives the hub URL from the
# host that SERVED the page — ws://<that-host>:8000/ws (wss when the page is
# https). So a tablet that loads the UI from http://<ubuntu-ip>:5173 connects to
# ws://<ubuntu-ip>:8000/ws automatically; no IP baked into the build.
#
# Set it ONLY to point at a hub on a DIFFERENT host/port than the one serving the
# UI, e.g.:
# VITE_WS_URL=ws://192.168.1.50:8000/ws
#
# Or override just the port used by host-derivation (default 8000):
# VITE_WS_PORT=8000
